&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensemble Travel Group&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a leading travel agency consortium of top-tier agencies throughout the U.S. and Canada that was established in 1968. Part of Kensington Tours since June 2022, Ensemble provides members with access to exclusive offers, unique hosted tours, partnerships and superior marketing opportunities with best-in-class suppliers, and proprietary travel platforms such as ADX that offers agents instant commission visibility, one click insurance and more to improve efficiencies and earnings. Ensemble maintains offices in Toronto and New York.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ensemble is seeking a results-driven Director, Partner Relations (Hotels) to lead and grow strategic hotel supplier partnerships. Reporting to the Senior Director, Partner Relations (Hotels), this role is accountable for supplier strategy, revenue growth, and program performance across preferred hotel partners. The ideal candidate brings deep hotel industry expertise, strong commercial acumen, and the ability to translate relationships into measurable results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supplier Strategy &amp;amp; Relationships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and grow hotel supplier partnerships at both chain/brand and property levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, pitch, onboard, and manage new hotel suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive participation in preferred programs, special offers, enhanced commissions, and marketing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and launch supplier programs that clearly communicate value, opportunities, and ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with suppliers on incentives, promotions, and events; track and report outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Member Relations to ensure strong adoption of hotel programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support member onboarding, agency training, and supplier-related escalations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Performance &amp;amp; Business Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute soft-dollar monetization strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead supplier business reviews, performance tracking, and optimization against revenue and profit targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sell and manage hotel marketing and advertising programs in partnership with Marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch revenue-driving initiatives grounded in Ensemble’s performance and growth strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate supplier agreements to improve revenue and profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communications &amp;amp; Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute hotel supplier communication strategies with Marketing and Advisor Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maximize existing channels and introduce new ones to increase supplier engagement and revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure effective dissemination of hotel product knowledge across the advisor network via events, digital channels, and proprietary platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong knowledge of hotel market trends and competitive landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Ensemble at industry events and supplier forums.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years’ experience managing hotel supplier relationships with budget accountability of $2M+.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success building programs that grow revenue and/or improve profitability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to pitch, sell, and execute complex programs with senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong negotiation, communication, and relationship management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience man

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensemble Travel Group&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a leading travel agency consortium of top-tier agencies throughout the U.S. and Canada that was established in 1968. Part of Kensington Tours since June 2022, Ensemble provides members with access to exclusive offers, unique hosted tours, partnerships and superior marketing opportunities with best-in-class suppliers, and proprietary travel platforms such as ADX that offers agents instant commission visibility, one click insurance and more to improve efficiencies and earnings. Ensemble maintains offices in Toronto and New York.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a detail-oriented and proactive intern to join our Partner Relations team. In this role, you&#39;ll support the day-to-day operations that keep our hotel, tour operator, and specialty partner programs running smoothly — from onboarding and troubleshooting to content management and cross-functional collaboration. You&#39;ll also have the opportunity to contribute to analysis and strategic initiatives, going beyond practical tasks to help the team think through challenges and opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update Member Portal sites with new content, product offers and contact information for preferred partners as directed. Reach out to partners on a quarterly basis to ensure sites are updated. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct audits of partner Member Portal profiles to identify missing information, outdated content, access gaps, and other items requiring follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot Member Portal issues such as login problems, broken links, profile visibility, and user setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support onboarding for new hotel, tour operator, and specialty partners, including account setup, access configuration, profile readiness, and early-stage questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Hotel team&#39;s shared inbox, handling partner inquiries and coordinating internal follow-ups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support analysis and strategic initiatives, helping the team surface insights, identify patterns, and inform decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams — including Marketing, Finance, and Operations — to support shared initiatives and business priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and comfort managing multiple tasks simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear written communication skills for both internal and partner-facing correspondence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An analytical mindset and interest in strategic thinking — you&#39;re curious about the &quot;why&quot; behind the work and eager to dig into data or problems when the opportunity arises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort experimenting with AI tools to support day-to-day work, such as drafting communications, summarizing information, or streamlining repetitive processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Microsoft Excel, Powerpoint and Outlook and comfort with learning new tools and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, follow-through mindset — you don&#39;t let things fall through the cracks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
